In a message dated 4/16/2002 10:47:53 AM Pacific Daylight Time, 
mikeanderso(-at-)hotmail.com writes:
> Has anybody else had a little trouble getting the link pin dust covers to go 
> on?  The diameter seems to be just a tad large.  I tried freezing them a 
> bit, still no go.  I'll file the edges down a little today, and then put 
> them in the freezer, and see if I can get them to go.  Anybody have any 
> suggestions?  

Hi Mike,
Those you do have to hammer into place since they are made for a press fit!  
Just try to not dent the dome of the link pin covers when doing this.  A raw 
hide hammer works well, hard rubber hammer next and your normal steel hammer 
will work when used with care.
Eric&Barb

